<h1>Lewis Walsh</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://lewiswalsh.com/now/">lewiswalsh.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Rural Essex
England
United Kingdom
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Freelance software engineer and semi-professional photographer.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I design and build elegant, stable, and fast software.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
The sense of well-being that comes from problem-solving makes the time I spend writing software feel worthwhile. While it is somewhat creative I find the true creativity of photography a nice balance. Ones and zeroes versus colour, composition, and tone. It's a nice split.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
There is greater life satisfaction in small, maybe even concurrent, sometimes short-lived projects than in chasing that one big job or career.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
'Remote' and 'Rework' by Jason Fried
</p>

